objectives.name: Primary Safety Objective
objectives.text: To assess the safety and tolerability of selonsertib (SEL), GS-0976, and GS-9674, administered alone or in combination, in subjects with bridging fibrosis or compensated cirrhosis due to NASH

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate changes in liver fibrosis, as measured by the NASH Clinical Research Network (CRN) classification, without worsening of NASH (defined as any increase in hepatocellular ballooning or lobular inflammation)

endpoints.name: Primary Safety Endpoint
endpoints.text: The safety of SEL, GS-0976, and GS-9674, alone or in combination... assessed during the study through the reporting of AEs, clinical laboratory tests, vital sign assessments, pruritus questionnaires, and concomitant medication usage.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Proportion of subjects at Week 48 who achieve a ≥ 1-stage improvement in fibrosis (according to the NASH CRN classification) without worsening of NASH (defined as a ≥ 1-point increase in hepatocellular ballooning or lobular inflammation).

estimands.name: Primary Safety Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adults (18-80 years) with bridging fibrosis (F3) or compensated cirrhosis (F4) due to NASH Summary measure: Frequency and severity of adverse events and laboratory abnormalities.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study drug due to AE or other reasons

estimands.treatment: SEL, GS-0976, and GS-9674 (alone or in combination) vs Placebo
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adults (18-80 years) with bridging fibrosis (F3) or compensated cirrhosis (F4) due to NASH
estimands.variableOfInterest: Safety and tolerability assessed through AEs, laboratory tests, vital signs, pruritus questionnaires, and concomitant medications
estimands.summaryMeasure: Frequency and severity of adverse events and laboratory abnormalities

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adults (18-80 years) with bridging fibrosis (F3) or compensated cirrhosis (F4) due to NASH Summary measure: Difference in proportions (point estimates and 95% confidence intervals).

intercurrentEvents.name: Hepatic decompensation
intercurrentEvents.text: Development of Child-Pugh score ≥ 7 or liver transplantation

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study drug prior to Week 48 biopsy

intercurrentEvents.name: Missing Week 48 biopsy
intercurrentEvents.text: Failure to obtain Week 48 liver biopsy for assessment
